The paper discusses the use of Multiple Input Multiple Output (MIMO) in Cognitive Radio (CR), which involves optimizing and sharing resources in the spatial domain. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), or Communications (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses power consumption in the context of spatial cognition, which could also place it in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
